                            <comment id="13214838" author="nspiegelberg" created="Thu, 23 Feb 2012 16:32:45 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I wonder if a good default would be some fraction of the flushsize. Maybe 1/4*flushsize, or something.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that we raised the min size so that we&apos;d aggressively compact the .META. table, which is normally pretty small.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13833748" author="neilf" created="Wed, 27 Nov 2013 12:46:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just wanted to reference this discussion: &lt;a href=&quot;http://search-hadoop.com/m/2tTzS4zXIS&amp;amp;subj=Re+COMPACTIONS+Anyone+seen+hbase+hstore+compaction+min+size+in+trunk+0+95+&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://search-hadoop.com/m/2tTzS4zXIS&amp;amp;subj=Re+COMPACTIONS+Anyone+seen+hbase+hstore+compaction+min+size+in+trunk+0+95+&lt;/a&gt; which appears to be the latest on this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
